header.gameNote: PHILLY HOOP GROUP CLASSIC AT PHILADELPHIA PA

article.headline: Siena 99, Brown 79
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Ronald Moore scored 19 points and dished out 11 assists, Clarance Jackson had 23 points and Siena dominated Brown in a 99-79 rout on Saturday. Alex Franklin finished with 21 points and six rebounds for the Saints (4-2) in the Philly Hoop Group Classic. Kyle Downey scored 11 points off the bench. Siena trailed 17-12 with 14:33 left in the first half, but the Saints followed with 17 straight points over the next 3 1/2 minutes to take a 12-point lead. Moore, who finished with five steals, had six points and two steals during the run. Jackson, who shot 8-for-12 from the field and 5-for-8 from beyond the arc, made a 3-pointer with 12:07 left to play to give Siena a 75-55 lead. He later hit back-to-back 3s to put Siena ahead by 26 points. Matt Mullery scored 23 points for the Bears (4-4). Andrew McCarthy had 18 points and 11 rebounds.
